Deputy President Ramaphosa says South Africans must not appoint what he calls &#8220;Mickey Mouse people&#8221; to manage the country&#8217;s affairs. JOHANNESBURG - Deputy President Cyril Ramaphosa says the Expanded Public Works Programme (EPWP) is aimed at playing a transformative role, to create 6 million jobs by 2019. Ramaphosa was speaking at the opening of the Expanded Public Works Programme summit in Pretoria on Tuesday.#PublicWorksSummit Ramaphosa: We must get the best people to manage the affairs of the county - we must not have mickey mouse people. KSRamaphosa has called for an inter-corruption and mismanagement task team to be established. We do what we do for our people because we re compassionate. We want to take care of our people. Ramaphosa says South Africans must not appoint what he calls Mickey Mouse people to manage the country s affairs. We desire a South Africa that s corruption free. We desire a South Africa of men and women of integrity. The summit will review the progress made since the launch of phase three of the Expanded Public Works Programme in 2014.(Edited by Zamangwane Shange)